South African Crops Committee Cuts Corn Harvest Forecast 0.7%

-- B y   J a n a   M a r a i s
-- 
2011-09-27T13:30:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-27/south-african-crops-committee-cuts-corn-harvest-forecast-0-7-.html
South Africa ’s Crop Estimates
Committee cut its forecast for this season’s corn harvest by 0.7
percent to 10.6 million metric tons from its previous estimate.  The committee reduced its white-corn forecast by 0.3
percent to 6.2 million tons and its yellow-corn estimate by 1.2
percent to 4.4 million tons, spokeswoman Marda Scheepers said by
phone from  Pretoria  today.  The forecast for the total corn crop is higher than the
median estimate of 10.5 million tons of nine traders surveyed by
Bloomberg on Sept. 23.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jana Marais in Johannesburg at 
